Summary: Reported to cause congenital nephrotic syndrome, a rare recessive disorder that leads to kidney failure in infants and often lethal by a year or two of age. This classification comes from Juha Muilu Group; Institute for Molecular Medicine Finland (FIMM) (see Clinvar: http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/clinvar/RCV000049935/). Heeringa et al 2008 (PMID: 18503012) report seeing this variant once in a study of 32 affected children.
